    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-073",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row0_col1",
      "source_text": "EXPLANATION",
      "character_count": 11,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 1, column 2",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-074",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row1_col0",
      "source_text": "A service contract is a supply contract concerned with sourcing a service rather than a tangible product",
      "character_count": 104,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 2, column 1",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-075",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row1_col1",
      "source_text": "Company A wishes to purchase a service and enters into a contract with a selected supplier (Company B) to have the service performed on agreed terms",
      "character_count": 148,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 2, column 2",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-076",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row2_col0",
      "source_text": "Subcontracting is the use of an outside organisation to do work that the buying organisation cannot do itself, because of a temporary shortage of resources or lack of capacity",
      "character_count": 175,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 3, column 1",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-077",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row2_col1",
      "source_text": "Company A contracts Company B (the main contractor) to perform certain work, such as cleaning services. Company B lacks capacity to perform all the work itself. In order to meet Company A’s requirements, Company B subcontracts some of the work to Company C, if permitted to do so by its contract with Company A",
      "character_count": 310,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 3, column 2",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-078",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row3_col0",
      "source_text": "Outsourcing is the strategic contracting out of major work, previously carried out in-house, to an external service provider",
      "character_count": 124,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 4, column 1",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-079",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row3_col1",
      "source_text": "The outsourcer (Company A) will draw up a long-term contract specifying the work to be performed and the service levels to be achieved by an outsource provider (Company B). The outsourcer retains responsibility for satisfactory completion of the work, but delegates all day-to-day operations to the outsource provider",
      "character_count": 317,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 4, column 2",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-080",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row4_col0",
      "source_text": "Insourcing is the opposite of outsourcing",
      "character_count": 41,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 5, column 1",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-081",
      "slide_or_page": 29,
      "element_type": "table_cell",
      "element_id": "slide_29_Content_Placeholder_8_row4_col1",
      "source_text": "The organisation previously outsourced the work, but now decides to bring it in-house",
      "character_count": 85,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": true,
      "layout_context": "Table row 5, column 2",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
